         <change when="2026-04-22T03:56:21-04:00"
                 who="http://papyri.info/editor/users/ngonis">Submit - O.Wilck. 405 updated after P.Hoogendijk 14. The re-edition retained the resolutions διαγεγρ(άφηκεν) in lin1 and βαλ(ανικοῦ) in lin3, both of which are now considered untenable (the first one, in Thebes) and have therefore been corrected here. It also prints (ἥμ.), i.e. (ἥμισυ), in lin3 (twice), but this is now generally read as (ἡμιωβέλιον); the change has been made tacitly. The re-edition expresses some doubts about the revised reading of the personal names in lin1, but these look secure to me.</change>
